  "commentary": "With SPX at 6769.2 sitting between the negative gamma pocket at 6765 (-1742M) and the massive positive gamma wall at 6800 (+7868.9M), dealers are likely buying the current dip as they're short gamma below spot and will aggressively sell any push toward 6800. The PIN regime with 61.7B total GEX creates a strong mean-reverting environment, with the 6750-6800 corridor acting as a powerful magnet given the dense positive gamma walls clustered in this zone. Key levels to watch are 6765 (max neg gamma buying support) on the downside and 6800 (max pos gamma selling resistance) on the upside, with 6681 flip strike providing the lower boundary for continued dealer stabilization.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get pulled back toward the 6750-6800 range with dealers providing natural buying support here.",
